Interface RandomTeleportService

public interface RandomTeleportService
A tool for getting random positions in the world.

    • getLocationFuture

      CompletableFuture<Optional<org.spongepowered.api.world.server.ServerLocation>> getLocationFuture(org.spongepowered.api.world.server.ServerLocation currentLocation, RandomTeleportService.RandomTeleportOptions options)
      Search for a teleportation position in the target world.
      Async mode. Teleportation is only possible in the main thread.
      Despite the asynchrony, a large number of attempts to find a location can crash the server.
      Parameters:
      currentLocation - - The current location of the entity.
      options - - Options for finding a random position.
      Returns:
      ServerLocation

    • getOptions

      RandomTeleportService.RandomTeleportOptions getOptions(org.spongepowered.api.world.server.ServerWorld world)
      Getting options from the plugin configuration for the specified world.
      If no world is found, the default options will be selected.
      The method always returns a copy from the plugin configuration. Changing the copy will not affect the original values.
      Returns:
      RandomTeleportService.RandomTeleportOptions
